cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the co-membership network of a social platform. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper may discuss the technical aspects of constructing the co-membership network and applying social network analysis techniques. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper explores the interests and activities of a social platform's users in a specific location. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a less likely category, but may be relevant if the paper discusses any privacy or security concerns related to the meetup platform. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a less likely category, but may be relevant if the paper discusses the user experience and interface design of the meetup platform.
